        <num>159-C-1</num>
        <heading>Training; live fire conditions</heading>
        <content>
          <p>  ยง 159-c-1. Training; live fire conditions. 1. In the training of\nfirefighters under live fire conditions no person or persons shall play\nthe role of a victim.\n  2. For purposes of this section, a live fire condition is any\nunconfined open flame or device that can propagate fire to a building, a\ntraining tower, an acquired structure or other combustible material.\n  3. A violation of this section shall be punishable by a civil penalty\nnot to exceed one thousand dollars paid for by the fire department\nconducting such training.\n</p>
        </content>
      </section>
